<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Privacy Policy - Malaysia Pickleball Association</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/tailwindcss@2.2.19/dist/tailwind.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
  <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/all.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    .privacy-content {
      line-height: 1.8;
    }
    .privacy-content h2 {
      color: #1e40af;
      font-weight: bold;
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .privacy-content h3 {
      color: #1e40af;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }
    .privacy-content p {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .privacy-content ul, .privacy-content ol {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      padding-left: 2rem;
    }
    .privacy-content li {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .data-table {
      border-collapse: collapse;
      width: 100%;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    .data-table th, .data-table td {
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      padding: 0.75rem;
      text-align: left;
    }
    .data-table th {
      background-color: #f3f4f6;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-gray-50">
  <%- include('../partials/header') %>
  
  <main class="pt-20 pb-12">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 mb-8">
        <div class="text-center">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">
            <i class="fas fa-shield-alt text-green-600 mr-3"></i>
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg">Malaysia Pickleball Association</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Last Updated: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-MY', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' }) %></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Privacy Content -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 privacy-content">
        
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>The Malaysia Pickleball Association (MPA) is committed to protecting your privacy and personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal data when you register as a player, use our services, or interact with our website and platforms.</p>
        
        <p>This policy complies with the Malaysian Personal Data Protection Act 2010 (PDPA) and international privacy standards.</p>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3>2.1 Personal Information</h3>
        <p>When you register as a player with MPA, we collect the following personal information:</p>
        
        <table class="data-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Information Type</th>
              <th>Details</th>
              <th>Purpose</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Identity Information</td>
              <td>Full name, IC number, age, date of birth</td>
              <td>Player identification and verification</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Contact Information</td>
              <td>Email address, phone number, address, city, postcode</td>
              <td>Communication and event notifications</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Account Information</td>
              <td>Username, password (encrypted)</td>
              <td>Account access and security</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Profile Information</td>
              <td>Profile picture, playing preferences</td>
              <td>Player profile and identification</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Tournament Data</td>
              <td>Match results, rankings, statistics</td>
              <td>Performance tracking and rankings</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>2.2 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Website Usage Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, device information, pages visited</li>
          <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Session cookies for website functionality and user preferences</li>
          <li><strong>Log Files:</strong> Server logs for security and performance monitoring</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.3 Information from Third Parties</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Tournament organizers may provide match results and performance data</li>
          <li>Referees and officials may submit incident reports</li>
          <li>Medical personnel may provide health-related information (with consent)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <h3>3.1 Primary Uses</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Player Registration:</strong> Processing and managing your membership</li>
          <li><strong>Tournament Management:</strong> Entry processing, scheduling, and results management</li>
          <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Sending updates, announcements, and important notices</li>
          <li><strong>Rankings:</strong> Calculating and maintaining player rankings and statistics</li>
          <li><strong>Event Organization:</strong> Planning and coordinating tournaments and activities</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 Secondary Uses</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Sport Development:</strong> Analyzing trends to improve pickleball in Malaysia</li>
          <li><strong>Marketing:</strong> Promoting MPA events and activities (with opt-in consent)</li>
          <li><strong>Research:</strong> Anonymous statistical analysis for sport development</li>
          <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Meeting legal and regulatory requirements</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
        <p>We process your personal data based on the following legal grounds:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Consent:</strong> You have given explicit consent for specific processing activities</li>
          <li><strong>Contract:</strong> Processing is necessary for membership and tournament participation</li>
          <li><strong>Legal Obligation:</strong> Compliance with sports regulations and legal requirements</li>
          <li><strong>Legitimate Interest:</strong> Sport development and organizational activities</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <h3>5.1 Within MPA</h3>
        <p>Your information may be shared with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>MPA administrators and authorized staff</li>
          <li>Tournament directors and organizers</li>
          <li>Certified referees and officials</li>
          <li>State and regional pickleball associations</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.2 External Parties</h3>
        <p>We may share your information with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>International Pickleball Organizations:</strong> For international tournament eligibility</li>
          <li><strong>Sports Authorities:</strong> As required by Malaysian sports regulations</li>
          <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> IT support, payment processing, and event management</li>
          <li><strong>Medical Personnel:</strong> In case of emergencies during events</li>
          <li><strong>Legal Authorities:</strong> When required by law or court order</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.3 Public Information</h3>
        <p>The following information may be made publicly available:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Player name and MPA ID</li>
          <li>Tournament results and rankings</li>
          <li>Achievement records and statistics</li>
          <li>Profile pictures (if provided)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
        <h3>6.1 Security Measures</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> All sensitive data is encrypted in transit and at rest</li>
          <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> Role-based access with authentication requirements</li>
          <li><strong>Regular Backups:</strong> Secure backup systems with disaster recovery plans</li>
          <li><strong>Security Monitoring:</strong> Continuous monitoring for unauthorized access</li>
          <li><strong>Staff Training:</strong> Regular privacy and security training for all staff</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>6.2 Data Breach Response</h3>
        <p>In the event of a data breach, we will:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Notify affected individuals within 72 hours</li>
          <li>Report to relevant authorities as required by law</li>
          <li>Take immediate steps to contain and remedy the breach</li>
          <li>Provide support and guidance to affected individuals</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
        <h3>7.1 Retention Periods</h3>
        <table class="data-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Data Type</th>
              <th>Retention Period</th>
              <th>Reason</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Active Player Records</td>
              <td>Duration of membership + 2 years</td>
              <td>Membership management and historical records</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Tournament Results</td>
              <td>Permanent (anonymized after 10 years)</td>
              <td>Historical records and sport development</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Communication Records</td>
              <td>3 years</td>
              <td>Dispute resolution and compliance</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Financial Records</td>
              <td>7 years</td>
              <td>Legal and tax compliance</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Website Logs</td>
              <td>1 year</td>
              <td>Security and technical support</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>7.2 Data Deletion</h3>
        <p>When retention periods expire, we will:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Securely delete personal identifiers</li>
          <li>Anonymize statistical data for research purposes</li>
          <li>Maintain essential records as required by law</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Under the Malaysian PDPA and international privacy standards, you have the right to:</p>

        <h3>8.1 Access Rights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Request a copy of your personal data we hold</li>
          <li>Obtain information about how your data is processed</li>
          <li>Receive data in a portable format</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.2 Correction Rights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Update or correct inaccurate personal information</li>
          <li>Complete incomplete data records</li>
          <li>Request verification of data accuracy</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.3 Deletion Rights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Request deletion of your personal data (subject to legal requirements)</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent for processing (where applicable)</li>
          <li>Object to processing for direct marketing</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.4 Restriction Rights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Limit how we process your data</li>
          <li>Object to automated decision-making</li>
          <li>Request temporary suspension of processing</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>9. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <h3>9.1 Types of Cookies</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for website functionality and security</li>
          <li><strong>Performance Cookies:</strong> Help us improve website performance</li>
          <li><strong>Preference Cookies:</strong> Remember your settings and preferences</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>9.2 Cookie Management</h3>
        <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Note that disabling essential cookies may affect website functionality.</p>

        <h2>10. International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>Your data may be transferred internationally for:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>International tournament participation</li>
          <li>Cloud storage and backup services</li>
          <li>Technical support and maintenance</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We ensure adequate protection through appropriate safeguards and contractual obligations.</p>

        <h2>11. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Players under 18 require parental/guardian consent</li>
          <li>We take extra care to protect children's personal information</li>
          <li>Parents can request access to or deletion of their child's data</li>
          <li>Special protections apply to players under 13</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>12. Updates to This Policy</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>We may update this policy to reflect changes in law or practice</li>
          <li>Significant changes will be communicated via email and website notice</li>
          <li>Continued use of our services constitutes acceptance of updates</li>
          <li>Previous versions are archived and available upon request</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>13. Contact Information</h2>
        <h3>13.1 Data Protection Officer</h3>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg mt-4">
          <p><strong>Malaysia Pickleball Association - Data Protection Officer</strong></p>
          <p><i class="fas fa-envelope mr-2"></i>Email: privacy@malaysiapickleball.org</p>
          <p><i class="fas fa-phone mr-2"></i>Phone: +60 3-XXXX XXXX</p>
          <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt mr-2"></i>Address: [MPA Official Address]</p>
        </div>

        <h3>13.2 Complaints</h3>
        <p>If you have concerns about how we handle your personal data, you can:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Contact our Data Protection Officer directly</li>
          <li>File a complaint with the Personal Data Protection Department of Malaysia</li>
          <li>Seek legal advice regarding your privacy rights</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="mt-8 p-4 bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500">
          <p class="text-green-800"><strong>Your Privacy Matters:</strong> We are committed to protecting your personal information and will only use it as described in this policy. If you have any questions or concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500">
          <p class="text-blue-800"><strong>Consent:</strong> By registering with MPA and using our services, you consent to the collection and use of your personal information as outlined in this Privacy Policy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>